 normal conditions and after exposure to extreme temperatures. <\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n","answer_id":31579,"question_id":31574,"up_vote_count":2}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/31574/applying-kiwis-on-gelatin","last_activity_date":1429654204,"creation_date":1429644040,"answer_count":1,"title":"Applying kiwis on gelatin","body":"<p>Kiwis have the enzyme actinidain. This enzyme will break the peptide bonds from the gelatin. Making gelatin with raw kiwis will not work, because the peptide bonds in the gelatin will be broken down. <\/p>\n\n<p>But what if you would make plain gelatin, and apply raw kiwis to it? Do the enzymes break down the gelatin when the gelatin already has set?<\/p>\n","question_id":31574,"tags":["biochemistry","enzymes"],"score":3,"accepted_answer_id":31579,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":65,"up_vote_count":3,"last_edit_date":1429644736},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/3d175379c9045d416d6e64c0c1bbd489?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":15440,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/15440/rozmarin","reputation":76,"display_name":"rozmarin"},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/31f7489ce1ad16353c71abba83ae8be4?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":4747,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4747/user137","reputation":3897,"display_name":"user137","accept_rate":78},"score":0,"post_id":31572,"edited":false,"creation_date":1429639126,"comment_id":52970,"body":"I can&#39;t tell if those have 6 legs and large antenna, or 8 legs and no antenna. If 8 legs, then I suspect some sort of mite."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/85bb9e2c9145ecb17430d6fdb574410f?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":12909,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/12909/dustin","reputation":2006,"display_name":"dustin"},"score":0,"post_id":31572,"edited":false,"crea