ly. However, this is only a future direction and we still can not say its fit for a knockout.(Patrick D. Hsu, Eric S. Lander, and Feng Zhang, (2014) Development and Applications of CRISPR-Cas9 for Genome Engineering. Cell 14(6): 1262-1278)\nAnd for editing some cell gene in a limited area, some research are on going for therapeutic purpose (Liqun Zhang et al.CFTR Delivery to 25% of Surface Epithelial Cells Restores Normal Rates of Mucus Transport to Human Cystic Fibrosis Airway Epithelium), but haven't seen research are trying to built KO cell in vivo.<\/p>\n","answer_id":31551,"question_id":31526,"up_vote_count":1}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/31526/is-it-possible-to-knock-out-a-gene-in-adults","last_activity_date":1429588327,"creation_date":1429550759,"answer_count":1,"title":"Is it possible to knock out a gene in adults?","body":"<p>gene knockout is mainly used in creating newborn animals... right? Well can you do it to already-adult animals or humans so that they themselves would experience change in their body and not just their off springs?<\/p>\n","question_id":31526,"tags":["genetics"],"score":1,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":104,"up_vote_count":1},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/73cb4730cf40c0297fe57a2fd07f7e2f?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":13409,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/13409/joshua-benabou","reputation":173,"display_name":"Joshua Benabou"},"closed_date":1429606324,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/85bb9e2c9145ecb17430d6fdb574410f?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":12909,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/12909/dustin","reputation":2006,"display_name":"dustin"},"score":0,"post_id":31550,"edited":false,"creation_date":1429588377,"comment_id":52916,"body":"Prolonged exposure to cyanobacteria is generally related to neurological diseases, <a href=\"http://www.