g simple genomes.<\/p>\n\n<p>Note that the basic requirement really depends on how you define life. Is a virus alive although it has no metabolism? Would a self-replicating RNA be a living thing? Because we were able to artificially synthesize self-replicating RNA. While the subject is interesting, the main issue is a purely philosophical one: How do you define life?<\/p>\n","answer_id":22009,"question_id":22008,"up_vote_count":1}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/22008/simplest-biological-organism","last_activity_date":1429488029,"creation_date":1412893922,"answer_count":1,"title":"Simplest Biological Organism?","body":"<p>What is the simplest biological organism from which a DNA sample has been or could be obtained?  Could the resulting DNA be processed and examined in such a way that the resulting information would give biologists a rudimentary understanding of life's minimal requirements?  <\/p>\n","question_id":22008,"tags":["evolution","dna","dna-sequencing","genomes"],"score":0,"down_vote_count":0,"closed_reason":"duplicate","is_answered":true,"view_count":69,"up_vote_count":0,"last_edit_date":1429488029},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/Ubbmd.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":5729,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/5729/katherinebridges","reputation":372,"display_name":"katherinebridges","accept_rate":94},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/da1e8af33e12bfa60ea44b3af00c0d03?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"moderator","user_id":5144,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/5144/chris","reputation":31001,"display_name":"Chris"},"score":0,"post_id":31453,"edited":false,"creation_date":1429299491,"comment_id":52719,"body":"What is the source of this claim?"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/Ubbmd.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":5729,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/5729/katherinebridges","reputation