<\/a> do (considering same alcohol content consumed). <\/p>\n\n<p>My understanding is that a hangover is <a href=\"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/5087/what-is-the-molecular-basis-of-hangovers\">nothing more than dehydration caused by alcohol<\/a>. More alcohol per unit of mass - more dehydration.<\/p>\n\n<p><strong>Is there any biological evidence to show that the same amount of alcohol consumed (with a different type of yeast) per same body mass would have different effects?<\/strong> <\/p>\n","question_id":31476,"tags":["human-anatomy","metabolism","alcohol"],"score":0,"down_vote_count":1,"is_answered":false,"view_count":99,"up_vote_count":1,"last_edit_date":1429454577},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/55DUG.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":15368,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/15368/rockpaperlizard","reputation":169,"display_name":"RockPaperLizard"},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/b10de963b115fd0720d6a558fd1ac06c?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":10456,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/10456/march-ho","reputation":5867,"display_name":"March Ho","accept_rate":80},"score":2,"post_id":31427,"edited":false,"creation_date":1429220161,"comment_id":52637,"body":"I can&#39;t say anything about the bacteria in yogurts (usually <i>Lactobacillus<\/i>) but labs routinely freeze <i>E. coli<\/i> to -80 degrees C without killing them."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/31f7489ce1ad16353c71abba83ae8be4?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":4747,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4747/user137","reputation":3897,"display_name":"user137","accept_rate":78},"score":2,"post_id":31427,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/b10de963b115fd0720d6a558fd1ac06c?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":10456,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/use