 than hormone B, then  A is 5 times more active than B. This is not the best definition / example but I think you can get the point from this."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1YczA.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":9943,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/9943/christiaan","reputation":26721,"display_name":"Christiaan","accept_rate":93},"score":3,"post_id":31334,"edited":false,"creation_date":1429022819,"comment_id":52411,"body":"This question is not broad and pretty well focused. I did a literature search and it is actually hard to find! In all a good question from my point of view +1."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/Ic4na.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":14735,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/14735/nandor-poka","reputation":2578,"display_name":"Nandor Poka","accept_rate":75},"score":0,"post_id":31334,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1YczA.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":9943,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/9943/christiaan","reputation":26721,"display_name":"Christiaan","accept_rate":93},"edited":false,"creation_date":1429036641,"comment_id":52424,"body":"@AliceD - I have to disagree with you on this one. I think we both agree that the effect of a hormone or any biologically active molecule can be measure in several ways, eg gene expression by RT PCR, flurescent riporter gene, riporter gene activity assay etc. and that&#39;s just one thing and few examples. This in my view is too broad. But on the other hand I might interpret the question in the wrong way...."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/acb3c0063d438705f86396a8abc1b04a?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":12877,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/12877/cmosychuk","reputation":4410,"display_name":"CMosychuk"},"score":1,"post_id":31334,"edited":false,"creation_date":1429047466,"comment_id":52442,"body":"If you think about a jackhammer, the better effector is the one that can chip away the most concrete. If the jackhammer had low power or no power (T4), we can safely imagine you&#39;d have lower efficacy than the full-power jackhammer (T3). We can measure the activity of a jackhammer as a function of the work done vs. power provided. In much the same way, we can measure biological activity as a function of concentration vs. catalytic/binding activity. All they&#39;re saying is that T3 has more activity at comparable concentrations to T4. Plasmon surface resonance can help measure binding/interactions."}],"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/376777bd35c33bb78d086b68a261b50d?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":12972,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/12972/niftyname","reputation":85,"display_name":"NiftyName"},"score":1,"is_accepted":false,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1YczA.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":9943,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/9943/christiaan","reputation":26721,"display_name":"Christiaan","accept_rate":93},"score":0,"post_id":31346,"edited":false,"creation_date":1429044543,"comment_id":52437,"body":"Thanks for answering! Could you back these figures up with a reference or two?"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/ZBeuU.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":9020,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/9020/look-behind-you","reputation":808,"display_name":"Look behind you","accept_rate":100},"score":0,"post_id":31346,"edited":false,"creation_date":1429072253,"comment_id":52466,"body":"It is unclear what you mean by &quot;produced at rate 3-5x of T4&quot; because 90% of all hormonal output from thyroid is T4, but T4 later get converted to T3 at liver and kidney. Do you mean the net total T3 present in the body at any given time? The sadly text is also unclear what 