ology.stackexchange.com/users/5144/chris","reputation":31001,"display_name":"Chris"},"score":2,"post_id":31385,"edited":false,"creation_date":1429123177,"comment_id":52535,"body":"This is a complete citation from the paper and not well liked here. Please answer the question in your own words and use the reference to back up what you say."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-lTPAMFBK_zM/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAKQ/_1pYTDEYkCc/photo.jpg?sz=128","user_type":"registered","user_id":15321,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/15321/westernbl%c3%b6d","reputation":302,"display_name":"WesternBlöd"},"score":2,"post_id":31385,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/da1e8af33e12bfa60ea44b3af00c0d03?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"moderator","user_id":5144,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/5144/chris","reputation":31001,"display_name":"Chris"},"edited":false,"creation_date":1429160416,"comment_id":52572,"body":"Sorry, error due to being new to the format. Edited appropriately."}],"down_vote_count":0,"last_activity_date":1429160941,"creation_date":1429122383,"body":"<p>The difference between secretion of ACTH  and neurohypophysial hormones is that the prior is a two step process, with CRF from hypothalamus stimulating the anterior pituitary. The latter is produced and secreted from the same cell, only in different organs! Magnocellular neurons stretch from the hypothalamus to the posterior pituitary, where they have their neurosecretory endings packed with hormone storing large dense-core vesicles. The same neurons are osmosensitive, regulating their secretion themselves as physiological need arises. Also, they apparently do dendritic secretion as autocrine signalling. Some reading about this: <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24265070\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24265070<\/a>\nand \n<a href=\"http://www.nature.com/nrn/journal/v7/n2/full/nrn1845.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.nature.com/nrn/journal/v7/n2/full/nrn1845.html<\/a>\nHope it helps.<\/p>\n","answer_id":31385,"question_id":31338,"up_vote_count":1,"last_edit_date":1429160941}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/31338/does-hypothalamus-regulate-posterior-pituitary-gland","last_activity_date":1429160941,"creation_date":1429030301,"answer_count":1,"title":"Does hypothalamus regulate posterior pituitary gland?","body":"<p>We have the hypothalamus-anterior pituitary-endocrine axis, but is there a similar chain of command for posterior pituitary gland such that oxycotin and vasopressin are regulated by some tropic hormones?<\/p>\n","question_id":31338,"tags":["brain","endocrinology","hypothalamus"],"score":4,"accepted_answer_id":31385,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":40,"up_vote_count":4,"last_edit_date":1429119084},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/0ab8c38fd1f90f6f97bedcb859f4063c?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":15344,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/15344/chuse","reputation":133,"display_name":"chuse"},"closed_date":1429174574,"comments":[{"owner":{"user_type":"does_not_exist","display_name":"user15346"},"score":0,"post_id":31371,"edited":false,"creation_date":1429101194,"comment_id":52503,"body":"I think lose of leaves depend upon both external condition and internal condition .By internal I mean cell death (Programmed Cell Death )."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1YczA.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":9943,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/9943/christiaan","reputation":26721,"display_name":"Christiaan","accept_rate":93},"score":1,"post_id":31371,"edited":false,"creation_date":1429106472,"comment_id":52500,"body":"I edited the question to improve clarity. Please feel free to roll back. Nice question! +1"}],"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/2d50eaca20365c51634c9452835c50ab?s=128&d=