324509031,"body":"<p>Cellular respiration in plants is slightly different than in other eukaryotes because the electron transport chain contains an additional enzyme called <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alternative_oxidase\">Alternative Oxidase<\/a> (AOX). AOX takes some electrons out of the pathway prematurely - basically the energy is used to generate heat instead of ATP. <\/p>\n\n<p>The exact purpose of AOX in plants is still unclear. Plants will make more AOX in response to cold, wounding, and oxidative stress. We know of at least one plant (skunk cabbage) that exploits this pathway to generate enough heat to melt snow. <a href=\"http://scienceray.com/philosophy-of-science/hot-stinking-plants-and-thermogenesis/\">This link<\/a> gives a pretty good overview. <\/p>\n\n<p><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/6WL8Z.jpg\" alt=\"Eastern skunk cabbage melting a hole through the snow.\"><\/p>\n\n<p>(AOX is dear to my heart, since my first 3 years working in a laboratory were spent studying this gene &lt;3)<\/p>\n","answer_id":273,"question_id":222,"up_vote_count":35,"last_edit_date":1429071925},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/52bddd6ae812be4933dc7d26c41d96af?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":154,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/154/abe","reputation":446,"display_name":"Abe","accept_rate":67},"score":6,"is_accepted":false,"down_vote_count":0,"last_activity_date":1324533398,"creation_date":1324533398,"body":"<p>Yes, respiration is exothermic and plants (like all living things) respire.<\/p>\n\n<p>I think the effect of covering the plant has to more to do with reducing sensible heat loss , e.g. direct transfer of heat from plant to air) rather than latent heat loss (through evaporation). <\/p>\n\n<p>The cover is effectively reducing the mixing of the air near the plant (and closer to the temperature of the surface of the earth) with the free atmosphere (closer to the temperature reported by the weatherman)<\/p>\n","answer_id":281,"question_id":222,"up_vote_count":6}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/222/do-plants-produce-any-heat","last_activity_date":1429071925,"creation_date":1324307513,"answer_count":4,"title":"Do plants produce any heat?","body":"<p>Many plants (e.g. roses, palms) can be protected from frost during the winter if shielded with an appropriate coat that can be bought in garden shops. Do plants produce any heat that can be kept inside with these \"clothes\"?<\/p>\n","question_id":222,"tags":["plant-physiology","botany"],"score":34,"accepted_answer_id":273,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":6952,"up_vote_count":34,"last_edit_date":1324310388},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/Bl9q8.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":15340,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/15340/sickest","reputation":113,"display_name":"Sickest"},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/889548c1e8387b3d381853dee5212cfd?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":3632,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3632/shigeta","reputation":22684,"display_name":"shigeta","accept_rate":86},"score":1,"post_id":31360,"edited":false,"creation_date":1429064093,"comment_id":52457,"body":"a) algae b) if it has formed a scummy biofilm, it might have to be harsh treatment to get it off. kerosene?"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/Bl9q8.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":15340,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/15340/sickest","reputation":113,"display_name":"Sickest"},"score":0,"post_id":31360,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/889548c1e8387b3d381853dee5212cfd?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":3632,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3632/shigeta","reputation":22684,"display_name":"shigeta","accept_rate":86},"edited":false,"creation_date":1429064319,"co